cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about image denoising using deep neural networks, specifically a dilated residual CNN. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of CNNs and the calculation of receptive field size, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of appropriate padding and the optimization of parameters, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The experiments conducted involve both gray and color images, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the use of dilated convolution and the optimization of performance suggest that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
